We discussed the K2 project that they have had to help quite a bit on. Ken told me taht recently they have been okay, but from other talks with customers involved in that project, everyone at K2 has no idea how much material they actually need to work on. They haven't had to call in much, but because they are so wrapped up with the local chem companies / K2 and Dow I left the group a bucket of redvines. I told him that I would make sure he is getting alerts to his email as well, saying that I undestand his customers will come to him wanting all the details in an urgent shipment. Ken and Marty sit in the office on the right , Joe works at the will call counter. I also spoke with Robert in the will call right when I first walked in. Nice guy, only handles the will call (in person) orders, not much on the phone.
